        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "From times to times I get this exception raised when requesting this uri : http:\/\/feeds.feedburner.com\/WebsitePlanning\nThe exact error message is \"Invalid chunk size \"<\" unable to read chunked body'\"\n\nHere is a sample code I use to request this uri :\n{code}<?php\n$client = new Zend_Http_Client();\n$client->setUri(\"http:\/\/feeds.feedburner.com\/WebsitePlanning\");\n$response = $client->request('GET');\n?>{code}\n\nIt is very weird because the exception is not always raised so I really do not know what could cause such issue.\nBTW I have tried to use file_get_contents function and it always returns a valid result so I think it is an issue into to socket adapter used by the http client....or maybe file_get_contents has a better handling of buggy responses ?"
        },
