                    "body": "another uri making this issue appears is : http:\/\/yd.blogspot.com\/2007\/01\/free-stuff-for-2007.html",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=slaanesh",
                        "name": "slaanesh",
                        "displayName": "Olivier Sirven",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-01-11T20:08:07.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-01-11T20:08:07.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12224",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm still trying to figure out what causes this - seems to be some kind of uncommon server behavior. I've noticed that the server ignores the 'Connection: close' request header and still replies with a 'Connection: keep-alive' response header.\n\nIn the mean time, a working work-around seems to be forcing the HTTP\/1.0 protocol version, which causes the server to obey \"Connection: close\" request headers. You can do that by setting this option:\n\n{code}$client->setConfig(array(\n\t'httpversion' => Zend_Http_Client::HTTP_0 \n));{code}\n\nbefore sending the request.\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-01-14T06:17:47.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-01-14T06:17:47.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12226",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "After minor modifications to Socket.php I think I solved the problem, although I am not sure (I can only prove this statistically - I am too tired right now to think why this solution works ;)\n\nPlease try with revision 2757 or later and let me know if this works better now.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-01-14T11:49:04.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-01-14T11:49:04.000+0000"
                },
